[ 1 ] British Computer Society [ 2 ] Information Retrieval Specialist Group
19 th Annual Colloquium on IR Research
8 - 9 April 1997 , Aberdeen , Scotland _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _
CALL FOR PAPERS _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _
Papers describing work in progress or completed work are invited on any topic related to Information Retrieval . Possible topics include , but are not limited to : * Evaluation and testing of information retrieval systems * Networked information retrieval * Hypermedia / Multimedia indexing and retrieval * Natural language processing for information retrieval * Logic and information retrieval * User interfaces for information retrieval * Information retrieval in library systems * Database and IR integration * Data mining and information extraction * Commercial applications of information retrieval systems * Data fusion
SUBMISSIONS
Authors are invited to submit electronically a copy of their paper , in English , to be received no later than 24 January 1997 . Papers should contain at most 7500 words and should be double-spaced . The first page must contain the title of the paper and an abstract of not more than 100 words , but no indication about the author ( s ) and affiliation ( s ) . In addition , authors must provide to the colloquium co-chair ( [ 3 ] bcs-irsg 97 @ scms . rgu . ac . uk ) an email message containing the title of the paper , the name of the file that has been subitted , the author name ( s ) , and the author affiliation ( s ) , plus complete contact information ( mailing address , telephone , fax and e-mail ) for the author to whom correspondence should be sent . Please indicate if the paper is to be considered for the Best Student Paper Award . This Award requires that the first and primary author be a full-time student at time of submission .
The organisation of the colloquium is planning to publish all or a selection of papers in the [ 4 ] electronic Workshops in Computing series , provided that the overall quality of papers is high enough . Therefore , authors should use the electronic submission format provided for the electronic Workshops in Computing series . Details of this format , and style files for LaTeX ( 2 e ) , RTF and PostScript are available at the [ 5 ] Springer Verlag web pages .
Please note : papers should not be submitted to the electronic Workshops in Computing editors directly ! Instead , a PostScript version of the paper should be submitted to the program co-chair ( for details , see the [ 6 ] submission guidelines ) .
As in previous years , a pre-print of the conference proceedings containing all accepted papers will be made available to attendees for use during the Colloquium . _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _
